# utility functions for cleaning columns
def get_word_count(text):
    return 0 if isinstance(text, float) else len(text.split())

def get_punctuation_count(text):
    return sum([0 if ((ch.isalnum()) or (ch == ' ')) else 1 for ch in text])

def get_all_caps_word_count(text):
    return 0 if isinstance(text, float) else sum(map(str.isupper, text.split()))

def get_repeat_word_count(text):
    if isinstance(text, float):
        return 0
    from collections import Counter
    word_counts = Counter(text.split())
    repeats = 0
    for word in word_counts:
        if word_counts[word] > 1:
            repeats += 1
    return repeats

# add new features
jobs['total_nan_vals'] = jobs.apply(lambda x: len(x) - x.count(), axis=1)

jobs['city'] = jobs.location.str.split(', ').str[-1]
jobs['descr_word_count'] = jobs['description'].apply(get_word_count)
jobs['descr_punct_count'] = jobs['description'].apply(lambda x: get_punctuation_count(str(x)))
jobs['descr_all_caps_word_count'] = jobs['description'].apply(get_all_caps_word_count)
jobs['descr_repeat_word_count'] = jobs['description'].apply(get_repeat_word_count)
jobs['co_profile_word_count'] = jobs['company_profile'].apply(get_word_count)
jobs['co_profile_punct_count'] = jobs['company_profile'].apply(lambda x: get_punctuation_count(str(x)))
jobs['co_profile_all_caps_word_count'] = jobs['company_profile'].apply(get_all_caps_word_count)
jobs['co_profile_repeat_word_count'] = jobs['company_profile'].apply(get_repeat_word_count)
jobs['requirements_word_count'] = jobs['requirements'].apply(get_word_count)
jobs['requirements_punct_count'] = jobs['requirements'].apply(lambda x: get_punctuation_count(str(x)))
jobs['requirements_all_caps_word_count'] = jobs['requirements'].apply(get_all_caps_word_count)
jobs['requirements_repeat_word_count'] = jobs['requirements'].apply(get_repeat_word_count)
jobs['missing_salary'] = np.where(jobs.salary_range.isna(), 1, 0)
jobs['missing_requirements'] = np.where(jobs.requirements.isna(), 1, 0)

# fucnction for the pivot plots
def show_pivot_plot(df, cols, grp_by_col, count_col):
    grpd = df[cols].groupby([grp_by_col, 'fraudulent'], as_index=False).count().rename(columns={count_col:'count'})
    pivot_df = grpd.pivot(index=grp_by_col, columns='fraudulent', values='count')
    pivot_df['fraud_percent'] = pivot_df[1] / pivot_df.sum(axis=1)
    pivot_df['real_percent'] = pivot_df[0] / pivot_df.sum(axis=1)
    pivot_df[['fraud_percent', 'real_percent']].plot.bar(stacked=True, color=["#74C476", "#006D2C"], figsize=(7,5),rot=0)
    plt.xlabel(grp_by_col)
    plt.ylabel('% of total')
    plt.legend(['yes','no'],title='fraudulent?')
    if len(df[grp_by_col].unique())>5:
        plt.xticks(rotation = 90)
    plt.show()

cols_to_pivot = ['employment_type', 'telecommuting', 'has_company_logo', 'has_questions',
                 'required_education', 'missing_salary', 'missing_requirements', 'function']
for col in cols_to_pivot:
    cols = [col, 'fraudulent', 'benefits']
    show_pivot_plot(jobs, cols, col, cols[2])
    
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Oversampling Functions for SMOTE¶

In [37]:
# find proportion of minority sample in data
def get_minority_proportion(y_vals):
    unique, counts = np.unique(y_vals, return_counts=True)
    cts_dict = dict(zip(unique, counts))
    majority_counts = cts_dict[0]
    minority_counts = cts_dict[1]
    minority_prop = minority_counts/(minority_counts+majority_counts)
    return minority_prop, minority_counts

# use SMOTE For oversampling minority class
def get_oversample(X, y):
    from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE
    sm = SMOTE()
    X_over, y_over = sm.fit_resample(X, y)
    minority_prop, _ = get_minority_proportion(y_over)
#     print(f'minority proportion in oversampled data: {minority_prop*100:0.2f}%')
    return X_over, y_over

Metric¶

In [51]:
# f2 score: 2X emphasis on recall, vs precision (minimize false negatives)
def get_f_beta_score(precision, recall, beta=0):
    f_beta_score = ((1 + beta ** 2) * precision * recall) / (beta ** 2 * precision + recall)
    return f_beta_score


# function to evaluate model performance on testing data
def get_eval_metrics(clf_name, ytrue, ypreds):
    accy = accuracy_score(ytrue, ypreds)
    conf_mtx = confusion_matrix(ytrue, ypreds)
    recall = np.diag(conf_mtx) / np.sum(conf_mtx, axis=1)
    precision = np.diag(conf_mtx) / np.sum(conf_mtx, axis=0)
    f1_score = 2*((precision*recall)/(precision+recall))
    f2_score = get_f_beta_score(precision, recall, beta=2)
    auc = roc_auc_score(ytrue, ypreds)
    metrics = {'conf_mtx': conf_mtx,
               'accuracy': accy,
               'auc': auc,
               'recall': recall,
               'precision': precision,
               'f1_score': f1_score,
               'f2_score': f2_score}
    return metrics

Model Fitting Functions¶

In [52]:
# functions for fitting model

def tune_hyperparameters(base_model, grid, X, y, scoring='auc'):

    print('***** Tuning Hyperparameters *****')
    random_model = GridSearchCV(estimator=base_model, param_grid=grid,scoring=scoring, cv=3, n_jobs=-1)
#     random_model = RandomizedSearchCV(estimator=base_model, param_distributions=grid, scoring=scoring,
#                                       random_state=30, n_iter=10, cv=3, n_jobs=-1)
    random_model.fit(X, y)
    return random_model.best_params_, random_model.best_score_

def fit_xgb(X, y, scoring='accuracy'):
    xgb_n_estimators = [100, 200, 500, 800]
    xgb_max_depth = [2, 5, 8]
#     xgb_min_child_weight = [1, 5, 9]
    xgb_eta = [0.1, 0.3, 0.4]
#     xgb_gamma = [0, 1, 4]

    xgb_grid = {'n_estimators': xgb_n_estimators,
                'max_depth': xgb_max_depth,
#                 'min_child_weight': xgb_min_child_weight,
                'eta': xgb_eta
#                 'gamma': xgb_gamma
               }
    
    spw = y[y==0].shape[0] / y[y==1].shape[0] # set weight to total_neg / total_pos
    base_model = XGBClassifier(objective='binary:logistic', eval_metric='aucpr', scale_pos_weight=spw)
    best_params, best_score = tune_hyperparameters(base_model, xgb_grid, X, y, scoring=scoring)
    print(f'best params for xgb: {best_params}\n')
    final_model = XGBClassifier(**best_params).fit(X, y)
    return final_model

def fit_lr(X, y, scoring='accuracy'):
    lr_solver = ['newton-cg', 'lbfgs', 'liblinear']
    lr_penalty = ['none', 'l1', 'l2', 'elasticnet']
    lr_C = [0.001,0.01,0.1,1,10,100]

    lr_grid = {'solver': lr_solver,
               'penalty': lr_penalty,
               'C': lr_C
               }
    
    base_model = LogisticRegression()
    best_params, best_score = tune_hyperparameters(base_model, lr_grid, X, y, scoring=scoring)
    print(f'best params for logistic regression: {best_params}\n')
    final_model = LogisticRegression(**best_params).fit(X, y)
    return final_model


def fit_rf(X, y, scoring='accuracy'):
    n_estimators = [100, 300, 500, 800, 1200]
    max_depth = [5, 8, 15, 25, 30]
    min_samples_split = [2, 5, 10, 15, 100]
    min_samples_leaf = [1, 2, 5, 10] 

    rf_grid = {'n_estimators': n_estimators, 
               'max_depth': max_depth,  
                'min_samples_split':min_samples_split, 
                'min_samples_leaf':min_samples_leaf
              }
    
    base_model = RandomForestClassifier()
    best_params, best_score = tune_hyperparameters(base_model, rf_grid, X, y, scoring=scoring)
    print(f'best params for random forest: {best_params}\n')
    final_model = RandomForestClassifier(**best_params).fit(X, y)
    return final_model

Function to put all steps together¶

In [53]:
# function to put all steps together
def fit_predict_eval_model(X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test, 
                                model='lr', scoring='auc',
                              resample=False):
    
    if resample:
        print('***** Oversampling Data *****')
        X_train, y_train = get_oversample(X_train, y_train)

        
    print('***** Fitting Model *****')
    if model == 'xgb':
        xgb = fit_xgb(X_train, y_train, scoring=scoring)
        print(f'xgb feature imps: {xgb.feature_importances_}')
        plt.bar(range(len(xgb.feature_importances_)), xgb.feature_importances_)
        plt.show()
        print('***** Getting XGB Predictions *****')
        y_train_preds = xgb.predict(X_train)
        y_test_preds = xgb.predict(X_test)

    elif model == 'lr':
        lr = fit_lr(X_train, y_train, scoring=scoring)
        print('***** Getting Logistic Regression Predictions *****')
        y_train_preds = lr.predict(X_train)
        y_test_preds = lr.predict(X_test)

    elif model == 'rf':
        rf = fit_rf(X_train, y_train, scoring=scoring)
        print('***** Getting Random Forest Predictions *****')
        y_train_preds = rf.predict(X_train)
        y_test_preds = rf.predict(X_test)
        
    print('***** Getting Performance Metrics *****')
    train_metrics = get_eval_metrics(model, y_train, y_train_preds)
    test_metrics = get_eval_metrics(model, y_test, y_test_preds)
    return train_metrics, test_metrics
